race.comment: STAY TUNED (9) up in grade and trip when a fading sixth in the soft (7) going over 1800m at Randwick in Midway grade. Gets a much better set-up for this back to the mile with regular rider going back on. Finds a fairly average BM64. UNCLE HARRY (8) settled at the rear then stoked up nicely in the straight to finish fourth over 1900m here last time. Must be included. SHURI (11) went back from the gate and failed to get into the contest when seventh over 1600m at Scone. Finds an easier contest with the key jockey change. MISSION TO WIN (4) is stepping out at this track for the first time. Last appeared when he finished second over 1900m at Kempsey on November 7. In the mix.
